[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"how do you add shortcuts to google sheets and google docs on a windows pc deaktop? I'll help you create desktop shortcuts for Google Sheets and Google Docs on your Windows PC. This is a straightforward process that will give you quick access to these tools without opening your browser first. Method 1: Using Google Chrome (Recommended) For Google Sheets: Step\tAction\tExpected Input\tExpected Output 1\tOpen Google Chrome browser\tClick Chrome icon\tChrome browser opens 2\tNavigate to Google Sheets\tType: sheets.google.com in address bar\tGoogle Sheets homepage loads 3\tAccess Chrome menu\tClick three dots (⋮) in top-right corner\tDropdown menu appears 4\tFind \"More tools\" option\tHover over \"More tools\" in menu\tSubmenu expands 5\tSelect \"Create shortcut\"\tClick \"Create shortcut\"\tDialog box opens 6\tName your shortcut\tType: \"Google Sheets\" (or preferred name)\tName field populated 7\tEnable desktop placement\tCheck \"Open as window\" box\tCheckbox selected 8\tCreate shortcut\tClick \"Create\" button\tShortcut appears on desktop For Google Docs: Step\tAction\tExpected Input\tExpected Output 1\tNavigate to Google Docs\tType: docs.google.com in Chrome address bar\tGoogle Docs homepage loads 2\tAccess Chrome menu\tClick three dots (⋮) in top-right corner\tDropdown menu appears 3\tFind \"More tools\" option\tHover over \"More tools\" in menu\tSubmenu expands 4\tSelect \"Create shortcut\"\tClick \"Create shortcut\"\tDialog box opens 5\tName your shortcut\tType: \"Google Docs\" (or preferred name)\tName field populated 6\tEnable desktop placement\tCheck \"Open as window\" box\tCheckbox selected 7\tCreate shortcut\tClick \"Create\" button\tShortcut appears on desktop Method 2: Manual Desktop Shortcut Creation Alternative Method: Step\tAction\tExpected Input\tExpected Output 1\tRight-click desktop\tRight-click on empty desktop space\tContext menu appears 2\tCreate new shortcut\tSelect \"New\" → \"Shortcut\"\tCreate Shortcut wizard opens 3\tEnter Google Sheets URL\tType: https://sheets.google.com\tURL field populated 4\tName the shortcut\tClick \"Next\" → Type \"Google Sheets\"\tShortcut named 5\tFinish creation\tClick \"Finish\"\tDesktop shortcut created 6\tRepeat for Docs\tUse URL: https://docs.google.com\tSecond shortcut created Method 3: Pin to Taskbar (Bonus Efficiency) Step\tAction\tExpected Input\tExpected Output 1\tOpen Chrome with Sheets\tNavigate to sheets.google.com\tGoogle Sheets loads 2\tAccess Chrome menu\tClick three dots (⋮)\tMenu opens 3\tCreate app shortcut\tSelect \"More tools\" → \"Create shortcut\"\tDialog appears 4\tEnable window mode\tCheck \"Open as window\"\tApp-like behavior enabled 5\tRight-click desktop shortcut\tRight-click the new shortcut\tContext menu shows 6\tPin to taskbar\tSelect \"Pin to taskbar\"\tIcon appears in taskbar Pro Tips for Maximum Efficiency: Rationale: These shortcuts will save you 15-30 seconds per access, and if you're using these tools 10+ times daily, that's 2.5-5 minutes saved daily (15+ hours annually). Additional Optimizations: Use keyboard shortcuts: Ctrl + T for new tab, then type your shortcut Set up bookmarks bar for even faster access Consider using Chrome profiles if you manage multiple Google accounts Expected Results: Desktop shortcuts will open Google Sheets/Docs in dedicated windows No need to navigate through browser bookmarks Faster startup times compared to opening browser first App-like experience with cleaner interface The Chrome method (Method 1) is recommended because it creates Progressive Web App (PWA) shortcuts that behave more like native applications, giving you a cleaner, distraction-free workspace perfect for your content creation and business management tasks. \"create shortcuts\" is not in the \"more tools\" dropdown I can see from your screenshot that you're looking at the Chrome menu and the \"More tools\" submenu is expanded. You're absolutely right - \"Create shortcut\" isn't showing in that submenu. Let me give you the correct updated method for creating Google Sheets and Docs shortcuts. Updated Method: Install as App (Chrome's New Approach) Chrome has changed how this works. Here's the current process: For Google Sheets: Step\tAction\tExpected Input\tExpected Output 1\tNavigate to Google Sheets\tType: sheets.google.com in Chrome\tGoogle Sheets homepage loads 2\tLook for install icon\tCheck address bar for install icon (⬇️ or computer monitor icon)\tInstall prompt may appear 3\tClick install icon\tClick the install icon in address bar\t\"Install Sheets?\" dialog appears 4\tConfirm installation\tClick \"Install\" button\tApp installs to desktop and Start menu Alternative Method (Address Bar Method): Step\tAction\tExpected Input\tExpected Output 1\tGo to Google Sheets\tNavigate to sheets.google.com\tSheets loads fully 2\tRight-click address bar\tRight-click on the URL area\tContext menu appears 3\tLook for \"Install\" option\tCheck for \"Install Google Sheets\" option\tInstall option shows 4\tClick install\tSelect install option\tDesktop shortcut created Manual Desktop Shortcut Method (Always Works): Step\tAction\tExpected Input\tExpected Output 1\tRight-click desktop\tRight-click empty desktop space\tContext menu appears 2\tCreate shortcut\tSelect \"New\" → \"Shortcut\"\tCreate Shortcut wizard opens 3\tEnter Sheets URL\tPaste: https://sheets.google.com\tURL field populated 4\tClick Next\tClick \"Next\" button\tName dialog appears 5\tName shortcut\tType: \"Google Sheets\"\tName field filled 6\tFinish\tClick \"Finish\"\tDesktop shortcut created 7\tRepeat for Docs\tUse: https://docs.google.com\tSecond shortcut created Chrome Three-Dot Menu Method (Updated Location): Step\tAction\tExpected Input\tExpected Output 1\tOpen Chrome menu\tClick three dots (⋮) as shown in your image\tMenu opens 2\tLook for \"Save and share\"\tClick \"Save and share\" (should be in main menu)\tSubmenu expands 3\tSelect \"Install page as app\"\tClick \"Install page as app\"\tInstall dialog opens 4\tConfirm installation\tClick \"Install\"\tApp shortcut created Rationale: Google moved this feature because they want to promote PWAs (Progressive Web Apps). The manual method is 100% reliable and gives you the same end result. Pro Tip: After creating the manual shortcut, right-click it and select \"Pin to taskbar\" for even faster access. This method works regardless of Chrome updates and gives you direct desktop access to your Google tools. The manual method I've outlined will definitely work and is actually more reliable than depending on Chrome's changing interface options. im setting up a pc with the most used apps for students. what are too apps..i already installed googlw doxs sheets and microsoft offixe. what are other food apps. unarchiver is in a mac. what is a good option for pc? I'll help you set up a comprehensive student PC with essential apps. Here's my strategic breakdown of must-have student applications: Core Student Apps (Priority Installation) File Management & Compression App\tPurpose\tExpected Input\tExpected Output\tRationale 7-Zip (Free)\tArchive management\t.zip, .rar, .7z files\tExtracted files/folders\tBest free alternative to Mac's Unarchiver - handles all formats WinRAR (Paid)\tPremium archiving\tAll archive formats\tCompressed/extracted files\tIndustry standard, better UI than 7-Zip PDF & Document Management App\tPurpose\tExpected Input\tExpected Output\tRationale Adobe Acrobat Reader\tPDF viewing/editing\tPDF files\tAnnotated/filled PDFs\tEssential for academic papers, forms Sumatra PDF (Lightweight)\tFast PDF viewing\tPDF, ePub, XPS files\tQuick document access\tFaster startup, less resource-heavy Note-Taking & Organization App\tPurpose\tExpected Input\tExpected Output\tRationale Notion\tAll-in-one workspace\tText, media, databases\tOrganized knowledge base\tPerfect for project management, research Obsidian\tKnowledge management\tMarkdown notes\tLinked note network\tGreat for research connections OneNote\tDigital notebook\tHandwritten/typed notes\tSearchable notebooks\tIntegrates with Office suite Communication & Collaboration App\tPurpose\tExpected Input\tExpected Output\tRationale Discord\tStudy groups/communication\tVoice, text, screen share\tReal-time collaboration\tEssential for student communities Zoom\tVideo conferencing\tMeeting links\tVideo calls/recordings\tStandard for online classes Slack\tProfessional communication\tTeam messages\tOrganized conversations\tPrepares for workplace tools Productivity & Focus App\tPurpose\tExpected Input\tExpected Output\tRationale Cold Turkey Blocker\tWebsite/app blocking\tDistracting sites list\tFocused work sessions\tProven to increase study productivity Forest\tPomodoro technique\tTimer settings\tGamified focus sessions\tMakes productivity engaging RescueTime\tTime tracking\tBackground monitoring\tProductivity reports\tShows where time actually goes Research & Reference App\tPurpose\tExpected Input\tExpected Output\tRationale Zotero\tCitation management\tAcademic sources\tFormatted bibliography\tEssential for research papers Grammarly\tWriting assistance\tText input\tGrammar/style corrections\tImproves academic writing quality Mendeley\tResearch management\tPDFs, citations\tOrganized research library\tGreat for thesis/dissertation work Media & Creative Tools App\tPurpose\tExpected Input\tExpected Output\tRationale VLC Media Player\tVideo/audio playback\tAll media formats\tPlayed content\tHandles any file format reliably OBS Studio\tScreen recording\tDesktop capture\tVideo recordings\tFree alternative to expensive screen recorders GIMP\tImage editing\tImages\tEdited graphics\tFree Photoshop alternative Canva Desktop\tDesign creation\tTemplates, images\tPresentations, graphics\tEssential for student presentations System Utilities App\tPurpose\tExpected Input\tExpected Output\tRationale CCleaner\tSystem cleanup\tSystem scan\tOptimized performance\tKeeps student PC running smoothly Malwarebytes\tSecurity scanning\tSystem files\tThreat removal\tEssential security for student PCs Everything\tFile search\tFile names\tInstant search results\tMuch faster than Windows search Installation Priority Matrix Tier 1 (Install Immediately) 7-Zip - Your Unarchiver replacement Adobe Acrobat Reader - PDF essentials Notion - Organization powerhouse Discord - Student communication VLC Media Player - Media essentials Zotero - Academic citations Tier 2 (Install Within Week) Cold Turkey Blocker - Focus enhancement Grammarly - Writing improvement OBS Studio - Recording needs Everything - File management Zoom - Class requirements Tier 3 (Install As Needed) Obsidian - Advanced note-taking Canva Desktop - Design projects GIMP - Image editing needs Mendeley - Heavy research projects Pro Installation Tips Rationale for Recommendations: Focus on free alternatives that match paid software functionality Prioritize cross-platform compatibility for group projects Choose apps that build professional digital literacy Select tools that integrate well with existing Google/Microsoft ecosystem Expected Time Investment: 2-3 hours for Tier 1 setup, additional 1-2 hours for customization and learning basic functions. Unique Innovation: Create a \"Student Productivity Stack\" by linking these apps together - use Notion to track assignments, Zotero for sources, Cold Turkey for focus sessions, and OBS for study session recordings. Would you like me to provide detailed installation and setup instructions for any specific apps from this list? is 7zip 64 bit? Yes, 7-Zip offers both 32-bit and 64-bit versions. Here's the breakdown: 7-Zip Version Options Version\tSystem Compatibility\tPerformance\tRecommendation 7-Zip 64-bit\tWindows 64-bit only\tFaster processing, more memory\tChoose this for modern PCs 7-Zip 32-bit\tBoth 32-bit & 64-bit Windows\tStandard performance\tOnly if you have old hardware How to Download the Right Version Step\tAction\tExpected Input\tExpected Output 1\tVisit official site\tGo to 7-zip.org\tOfficial download page loads 2\tIdentify your system\tCheck if your PC is 64-bit\tSystem architecture confirmed 3\tSelect correct download\tClick \"Download .exe 64-bit x64\"\t64-bit installer downloads 4\tInstall\tRun downloaded file\t7-Zip installed with 64-bit optimization Quick System Check To verify your Windows is 64-bit: Press Windows + R Type msinfo32 Look for \"System Type\" - should show \"x64-based PC\" Why Choose 64-bit Version? Performance Benefits: Handles larger archive files more efficiently Uses more available RAM for faster compression/extraction Better performance with multi-core processors Future-proofed for modern software Rationale: Unless you're running a very old PC (pre-2010), you should definitely use the 64-bit version. Modern student workloads often involve large file transfers, video projects, and software packages that benefit significantly from 64-bit processing. Expected Result: Faster file compression/extraction, especially noticeable when handling large project files, video content, or software installations that students commonly work with. The 64-bit version is the standard choice for any modern student PC setup. My pcs keeps having search.yahoo.com. As a default Chrome extension browser, but or the Chrome browser. But I want it to be google.com. How can I get this stealth mode? Search out of Yahoo and go to google.com as the main one when I go to settings? It's showing google, but it's the image of yahoo.So something is not right.This is a pc in This is a classic browser hijacking issue - Yahoo search is being forced despite your Chrome settings showing Google. This is common malware/adware behavior. Let me give you a comprehensive step-by-step solution. Immediate Fix Protocol Step 1: Check Chrome Extensions (Most Common Cause) Step\tAction\tExpected Input\tExpected Output 1\tOpen Chrome Extensions\tType: chrome://extensions/ in address bar\tExtensions page loads 2\tEnable Developer Mode\tToggle \"Developer mode\" switch (top right)\tShows more extension details 3\tIdentify suspicious extensions\tLook for unknown/recently added extensions\tList of all extensions visible 4\tRemove suspicious ones\tClick \"Remove\" on unknown extensions\tMalicious extensions deleted 5\tRestart Chrome\tClose and reopen browser\tClean browser restart Common Malicious Extension Names to Remove: Search Manager Yahoo Search Search Assistant Any extension you didn't install Extensions with random names/characters Step 2: Reset Chrome Search Settings Step\tAction\tExpected Input\tExpected Output 1\tOpen Chrome Settings\tClick 3 dots → Settings\tSettings page opens 2\tGo to Search Engine\tClick \"Search engine\" in left menu\tSearch settings visible 3\tCheck default engine\tVerify \"Google\" is selected\tShould show Google 4\tManage search engines\tClick \"Manage search engines and site search\"\tFull search engine list 5\tRemove Yahoo entries\tClick 3 dots next to Yahoo → \"Delete\"\tYahoo search removed 6\tSet Google as default\tClick 3 dots next to Google → \"Make default\"\tGoogle confirmed as default Step 3: Check for Malware (Critical Step) Step\tAction\tExpected Input\tExpected Output 1\tDownload Malwarebytes\tGo to malwarebytes.com\tDownload free trial 2\tInstall and run scan\tFull system scan\tMalware detection results 3\tRemove detected threats\tFollow removal prompts\tClean system 4\tRun Windows Defender scan\tWindows Security → Virus scan\tSecondary malware check Step 4: Reset Chrome Completely (Nuclear Option) Step\tAction\tExpected Input\tExpected Output 1\tOpen Chrome Settings\tSettings → Advanced → Reset\tReset options visible 2\tReset settings\tClick \"Restore settings to original defaults\"\tReset confirmation dialog 3\tConfirm reset\tClick \"Reset settings\"\tChrome restored to defaults 4\tReconfigure preferences\tSet up Google account, bookmarks\tPersonalized clean Chrome Advanced Troubleshooting Check Windows Hosts File Step\tAction\tExpected Input\tExpected Output 1\tOpen Command Prompt as Admin\tRight-click Start → \"Command Prompt (Admin)\"\tAdmin command window 2\tNavigate to hosts file\tType: notepad C:\\Windows\\System32\\drivers\\etc\\hosts\tHosts file opens 3\tCheck for redirects\tLook for google.com redirects to Yahoo\tIdentify malicious entries 4\tRemove bad entries\tDelete lines redirecting Google to Yahoo\tClean hosts file 5\tSave and restart\tSave file → restart computer\tSystem uses clean DNS Check Installed Programs Step\tAction\tExpected Input\tExpected Output 1\tOpen Programs & Features\tControl Panel → Programs → Uninstall\tInstalled programs list 2\tSort by install date\tClick \"Installed On\" column\tRecent installs at top 3\tRemove suspicious software\tUninstall unknown recent programs\tMalware programs removed 4\tCheck for toolbars/search apps\tLook for Yahoo-related software\tRemove Yahoo components Prevention Protocol Secure Chrome Settings Setting\tAction\tExpected Result\tSecurity Benefit Safe Browsing\tSettings → Privacy → Enhanced protection\tWarning on malicious sites\tPrevents future infections Pop-up Blocker\tSettings → Privacy → Site Settings → Pop-ups\tBlocks unauthorized pop-ups\tReduces malware exposure Extension Source\tOnly install from Chrome Web Store\tVerified extensions only\tPrevents malicious extensions Expected Outcomes Immediate Results: Google search restored as default Yahoo redirects eliminated Faster browsing performance No more unwanted search results Long-term Benefits: Protected against future browser hijacking Improved system security Better search result relevance Enhanced privacy protection Rationale: Browser hijacking typically happens through bundled software installations or malicious extensions. The multi-step approach ensures we eliminate the source, not just the symptoms. Pro Tip: Always choose \"Custom Installation\" when installing software and uncheck additional toolbars/search engines. This prevents 90% of browser hijacking attempts. Start with Step 1 (Extensions) as this fixes most cases immediately. Let me know which step resolves your issue, and I can provide more targeted assistance if needed. Super Agent Genspark Claw Free Trial +13 Ultra Speak"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=5c44b558-bd9e-4a10-9b47-532e5b3e91ce","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=5c44b558-bd9e-4a10-9b47-532e5b3e91ce"}]}]}]
